The food here is excellent. There's a good variety of sauces and you can pick two different sauces (split evenly amongst your wings, not mixed). There's also a wide selection of sides, with various seasonings for fries or options such as baked corn (small pieces of the cob, they put fry seasoning on and it is amazing). Despite the wonderful food I've had issues with the service. The employees, for the most part, aren't exactly providing great service. I'm pretty understanding about this usually but I'm giving three stars because in one instance they misheard my wife's order and gave her the wrong thing. Typically this would be an easy fix but they argued that they got it right at first. I've worked customer service before and I was shocked at that. Thankfully the last time I was there I saw a new employee who seemed to be doing a wonderful job, so hopefully this place improves with time.

Alright. So this is my second time grabbing food from here. Last time it was a Monday for lunch. This time it’s a Wednesday for dinner. The first time, the wings were good but I didn’t get my sauce. This time, they gave me the wrong wing flavor and one wing was missing. I understand that I should be checking my food before I leave but when I’m actually tellin a human or computer what I want, why not just follow the order? It really blows my mind that when I order online, I’m looking for convenience but I get the opposite. Both times I’ve waited until I got home to check the disappointment. I just want them to do better. I gave two stars because the staff has always been nice and the place is clean.

Ordered a 6 wing combo. Took 30 minutes. The wings were tiny and the fries literally tasted like cardboard. The last few times I went, the fries tasted like cardboard. The food just isn’t as good as it once was. Not wasting my money there anymore. The sauce was good though. But that’s it.
